<p class="eyebrow">Pricing</p>
<h1>Know what every minute, message, number, and lookup costs.</h1>
<p class="lede">VoiceTel pricing is built for buyers who want line-item math instead of bundled mystery. Compare minutes, messages, DIDs, emergency service, lookups, and optional voice features using source-dated public list prices.</p>
<p class="hero-actions">
	<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact/">Request pricing review</a>
	<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/voiceml/calculator/">Open calculator</a>
</p>

<section class="section-block" data-section-type="rate-table-copy">
	<h2>Rate table sections</h2>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Voice</strong> — Inbound local minutes, outbound US-50 and Canada minutes, toll-free inbound, AMD, recording, conferences, streams, transcription, and optional media features.</li>
		<li><strong>Messaging</strong> — SMS outbound, SMS inbound, MMS outbound, MMS inbound, carrier pass-through fees, A2P 10DLC, toll-free messaging, and campaign fees where applicable.</li>
		<li><strong>Numbers</strong> — Local number monthly, toll-free number monthly, emergency-service monthly, porting, CNAM, caller-ID, and number-type notes.</li>
		<li><strong>Lookups</strong> — CNAM, caller ID, LRN, MNP, carrier-of-record, batch pricing, and cache behavior.</li>
		<li><strong>SIP and PBX</strong> — Trunking, hosted PBX, SDN appliance, phone applications, and any monthly service fees is clearly separated from usage.</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section class="section-block" data-section-type="not-on-rate-sheet">
	<h2>What may be outside the rate sheet</h2>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Taxes and regulatory charges</strong> — Show them as excluded unless the rate file explicitly includes them.</li>
		<li><strong>Carrier pass-through fees</strong> — List separately and explain that carriers can change them.</li>
		<li><strong>Speech and storage vendors</strong> — If customers bring their own STT, TTS, or storage providers, state that those vendors bill separately.</li>
		<li><strong>Custom capacity</strong> — Large messaging or SIP workloads may require capacity review before final pricing.</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section class="section-block" data-section-type="source-note">
	<h2>Source note</h2>
	<p>Competitor list prices captured 2026-05-08 from publicly available pricing pages. Taxes, regulatory fees, surcharges, carrier pass-through fees, volume discounts, and contract pricing may vary.</p>
</section>
